page.title: 11Bird Survey
page.content: The wildlife in the area is very interesting and we did a bird survey over one week to give an idea of what can be found here.Crows and seagulls were not counted as there were so many. THURSH=12 BLACKBIRD=58 FIELDFARE=1 ROBIN=18 BLUE TIT=34 GREAT TIT=17 COAL TIT=2 BUZZARD=15 KESTRAL=4 BARN OWL=6 WOOD PIGEON=22 COLLERED DOVE=4 JAY=2 JACKDAW=38 CHAFFINCH=24 GREENFINCH=1 YELLOWHAMMER=5 CURLEW=5 HERON=9 MOORHEN=1 OYSTER CATCHER=9 MALLARD=13 PIED WAGTAIL=6 YELLOW WAGTAIL=1 MEADOW PIPIT=1 SKYLARK=7 HOUSE MARTIN=3 SWALLOW=35 SWIFT=2 TREE CREEPER=3 SPARROW=35 WREN=10 CUCKOO=2 STARLING=30. {SURVEY TAKEN IN MONIAIVE BETWEEN {22ND.APRIL AND 29TH. APRIL 1985.}
